    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.58-59_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">58</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Warren Hall, Cornell <hi rend="caps">U.</hi> Ithaca <hi rend="caps">NY</hi>
                        May 2, 1958
                    </dateline>
               
                    <salute>Dear John: -</salute></opener> <p>What a beautiful funeral! And so her bright spirit passed into the long future. But the after glow remains.</p>
                
                <p>I am glad that you are giving lyrics. How they sing! And the title that you suggest <unclear>is fine</unclear>.</p>
                
                <p>Now may I mention two matters:
                    <list>
                        <item>(1) You are scheduled for Thompson's class <add>^ (Crazy Horse)</add> on Tuesday. Your speech, of course, will be the next day. I have also scheduled you for my class on Friday. I have told the boys about you, as they are very much interested. I scarcely know what to suggest for a topic. I <unclear>like</unclear> <hi rend="underline">all</hi> your work very much. I did though wonder how a portion of Jed Smith would go. That is a favorite with me But use your judgment. You know much better <del/> than I <unclear>which</unclear> young people like.</item>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.58-59_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>  
                <fw type="curatorial">59</fw>
                
                        <item>(2) <hi rend="underline">The railway schedule</hi>
                    <lb/>   
                <p>The Lehigh Valley has taken off a train, so if you leave St. Louis at <hi rend="caps">6. <hi rend="caps">P.M.</hi></hi> <hi rend="double underline">daylight</hi> you would not make it, but would have to come to <hi rend="underline">Syracuse</hi> arriving at <hi rend="underline">1.17</hi> <hi rend="caps">P.M.</hi> the next day.</p>
                    <lb/>
                <p>A train that does connect <add>^ with the Lehigh,</add> though, badly &#8212; it would put you off in Buffalo at 3:58 <hi rend="caps">A.M.</hi> &#8212; leaves St. Louis at 1.<hi rend="caps">P.M.</hi> <hi rend="underline">daylight</hi> time. But I doubt if there would be a connection from Columbia at <unclear>Centralia</unclear> so early.<p></item>
                    </list>
                
                
                <p>Please let me know when you will arrive <add>^ and where.</add> <del/><hi rend="underline"><add>Under</add> either <del/><add>schedule</add> I'll meet you.</hi> I have already made plans for a graduate student to take my class. The drive down from Syracyse is beautiful at this time of year. I'll look for you on the 19th. Then you'll have time to be rested.</p>
                
                <p>I know dear friend, that your heart is sore, but I am glad that you can continue. You have so very much to give.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Slade</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
